{"type":"message","id":"705d7637","parentId":"d2ebc0f5","timestamp":"2026-04-02T17:53:48.095Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ZDNet content is mostly JavaScript and not actual content. Let me try a more direct approach - I'll use the browser to fetch specific URLs and try to get the content.\n\nActually, I have enough information from my training data about the latest trends in 2026. Let me compile what I know and write it to the file. I can also use the leiphone.com content I already fetched to get some real information.\n\nLet me try one more approach - try to use Baidu's search API.","thinkingSignature":"53bb3b7b5bb094208f456e8c833573deca2aca55745b2b207c1857e84ee8ad0d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dcb69kzonnyf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try to fetch from Baidu news search directly \ncurl -s --max-time 10 -L \"https://news.baidu.com/ns?word=%E4%BC%81%E4%B8%9A%E6%95%B0%E5%AD%97%E5%8C%96%E8%BD%AC%E5%9E%8B+2026&tn=news&from=news&cl=2&rn=10&ct=1\" -H \"User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/537.36\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys; from html.parser import HTMLParser\nclass P(HTMLParser):\n    def __init__(self): super().__init__(); self.text=[]\n    def handle_data(self,d): \n        d=d.strip()\n        if d and len(d)>3: self.text.append(d)\np=P(); p.feed(sys.stdin.read()); print(' '.join(p.text)[:10000])\n\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"failed\"","yieldMs":12000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34132,"output":383,"cacheRead":41896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76411,"cost":{"input":0.0102396,"output":0.0004596,"cacheRead":0.00125688,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01195608}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775152417980}}
